From: bilan@cps.msu.edu (Thomas J Bilan)
Subject: Re: Tiny-X
Date: 25 Oct 1993 02:50:38 GMT

dbonds@utxvms.cc.utexas.edu wrote:
: I'm currently running a 386-25 with 4megs of RAM and don't have the power to
: run X-Windows..  I've been running Linux for a very short period of time and
: would like a GUI interface if at all possible (at least until I learn the OS
: better).  I've been told about a smaller version of X called Tiny-X.  Would
: this run reasonably well on my system (3.95 Bogomips)?  Where could I get a
: copy of this?

:       - Danny
I have a Compaq 386DX-20 and I'm running the tinyX distribution successfully.
Believe me, it was painful to install mainly because the Compaq video 
controller suc*s and I had to disable it and put in a Trident 9000.  It's
slow but works fine.  If you don't have a swap space you might want to make
one.  I have 10 meg of swap space and I'm using it all the time.

You can find the tinyX dist at sunsite.unc.edu.

I think it's in the directory /pub/Linux/X11/tinyx but don't hunt me down
if it's not but it's close.

Good luck.
Tom Bilan
